column1: Adding new language in all Unit Test class for Accounting CBC
column7: SAP Reinsurance Management for SAP S/4HANA
column29:
Add additional polish language﻿ in all unit test classes for accounting CBC.


Review Comments from Code Red Team

Test data in the mock-up is currently set only in sy-langu. It would be beneficial to include another language in the mock-up as well, such as Polish. For reference, you can check the test class /msg/tc_cbc_lossstat_read_o4.  As a background info: unit test execution is performed in the language, in which the test class was created (German in our case, so variable sy-langu is filled with DE). In the future, when we switch to English as a development language, this will be English of course. So if you choose a Polish (PL) as a second mockup test language, this would be fine. This applies to all text entities within this service

column7: SAP Reinsurance Management for SAP S/4HANA
column196:
15/Dec/25 3:10 PM;712020:18187fe5-0ec8-4f23-9ef1-54b6e07dd101;I have given the Applicability status of IC standards respect with Treaty group CBC OData services. The OData service for Treaty Group Type, Status, and Reason for Change has been developed following SAP Clean Core principles and IC standards.

|*AP Product Standard*|*Status*|*Comments*|*Role*|
| | | | |
|Accessibility|Not Applicable|The OData CBC service is a backend API that only exposes data through service endpoints for consumption by other applications. It does not include any user-facing UI elements, screens, or interactive components such as buttons, menus, or navigation. There is no rendering of text, images, multimedia, or visual/auditory content, nor any user input or error handling in a UI context. Therefore, accessibility requirements related to UI design, labeling, navigation, and interaction are not applicable|User Story (End)|
|Business Configuration|Not Applicable|Not applicable because the OData CBC service does not manage or store configuration data It only exposes Treaty Group fields via API and does not involve configuration storage design.Since it is backend service, does not include anu UI configuration| |
|Functional Correctness|Passed|The OData service has been tested for functional correctness. All entity sets and operations return accurate and consistent data as per the defined Treaty Group Type, Status, and Reason for C.hange fields. we follwed the  coding rules, tested the new functionality added and existing functionality. They are working Eg: ATC Check and Versions are validated no error|User Story (End)|
|Globalization|Passed|The OData CBC service exchanges multilingual data via XML/JSON formats, requiring UTF-8 encoding and full Unicode support to prevent corruption and ensure global compatibility. It exposes text fields (e.g., Group Type, Group Status) that must support translation, locale-specific sorting, fallback languages, and personalization settings for date, time, and currency formats. These measures ensure the service can operate consistently across regions, comply with SAP’s globalization strategy, and meet internationalization requirements.|User Story (End)|
|Integration|Not Applicable|The OData CBC service is a standalone backend API exposing Treaty Group fields via endpoints.
It does not involve SAP-to-SAP or cross-application integration scenarios.
No Single Sign-On, Kernel Services, or interoperability frameworks are implemented.
The scope is limited to data exposure through OData, not enterprise-level integration.| |
|Licensing|Not Applicable|The OData CBC service does not use or distribute any commercial, open-source, or third-party software components.
It is a custom backend API built entirely with SAP standard technologies (CDS views, OData services) without external dependencies.| |
|Operations&Support|Passed|Operational documentation and backup/recovery ensure smooth deployment and business continuity.
Logging, monitoring, and secure support access enable troubleshooting and performance tracking.
Data lifecycle management and legal retention compliance safeguard Treaty Group data integrity.
High availability and consistency measures maintain reliability and stable performance in production. Eg: Field alias names are strictly verified with GTNC|User Story (End)|
|Performance |Passed|A performance test strategy ensures the OData CBC service meets response time and scalability requirements under realistic load conditions.
Capacity modeling is needed to estimate resources like CPU, memory, and network for efficient handling of Treaty Group data.
Throughput and end-to-end response times for API calls must be planned, measured, and verified for optimal performance.
Regression checks prevent performance degradation in future releases, and scale-up/scale-out capabilities ensure the service can handle growing data volumes and user requests.|User Story (End)|
|Security|Passed|The service complies with SAP security guidelines, including proper authorization checks and no exposure of sensitive data. If specific for authorization we have access control to implement. This Odata service authorization is not required. We can control them in coding level which is Access control point in CDS Views|User Story (End)|
|Software Lifecycle|Passed|The service is developed following SAP software lifecycle standards, including transport management and version control. So they have sequential process for Development, importing the objects and down porting and Testing process|User Story (End)|
|User Assistance|Not Applicable|No end-user documentation is required as the service is technical and consumed by other applications rather than direct users.|Epic Discussion|
|UX Consistency|Not Applicable|The service does not involve any UI components; hence UX consistency standards do not apply.|User Story (End)|

 

# The OData service for Treaty Group Type, Status, and Reason for Change has been developed following SAP Clean Core principles and IC standards.

# All applicable areas have been validated and passed, ensuring functional correctness, security, performance, globalization, and lifecycle compliance.

# Non-applicable areas have been justified based on the technical nature of the service (system-to-system integration, no UI involvement, no business configuration). This implementation is fully aligned with enterprise guidelines for maintainability, supportability, and future extensibility.

 
Regards
Balamurugan Natrayan

As a developer, i should write as many unit tests as possible to ensure code quality



*Note*:

* It is sufficient to add just one test in zephyr listing the epic and story id that should be used to execute the test
* Link all relevant zephyr tests in user story
* There must be a test cycle at epic level where these zephyr tests are executed

|Group Indicator   -  /MSG/RGRPZU_BEST|

Further, checked with PP if they can be part of Basic view. Suggestion from PP to clarify with technical team how they are maintaining the database for base view. Upon investigation, findings are as follow: maintaining database is not consistent, whether we can keep all fields or skip some.

As discussed we are keeping Extension Service and skipping other fields for base view.
